  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals in certain industries are typically obligated to report suspicious transactions or activities to designated authorities. Specific requirements can vary by jurisdiction, but generally include:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n2. Know Your Customer (KYC) compliance\n3. Transaction monitoring\n4. Record-keeping requirements\n5. Potential penalties for non-compliance\n\nI can provide general information about money laundering reporting requirements, but specific legal details would depend on the particular country and context.",
